    "faq_with_image_m73Xra": {
      "type": "faq-with-image",
      "blocks": {
        "accordion_GhRGXt": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "Do you create bespoke shaped bands to fit my engagement ring?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>Yes, this is one of our specialities. If your engagement ring has an unusual shape or low setting, our master goldsmiths can create a custom contour band that sits perfectly flush against it, ensuring a seamless fit.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_HmVJLJ": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "How far in advance should we order our wedding rings?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>For bespoke designs and shaped contour bands, we recommend starting the process 2 to 3 months before your wedding date. This allows ample time for CAD design approvals, casting, and any final size adjustments.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_xFhTbU": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "Can we design our rings online if we live in {{ block.settings.page.metafields.custom.location.value }}?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>Absolutely. Our Online 3D Design Studio is available to clients everywhere. You can fully customise your wedding bands online, and if you require assistance, you can easily request a home visit or video consultation.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_pxHnfz": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "Do our wedding rings have to match?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>Not at all! While some couples love the tradition of matching bands, we encourage you to choose a ring that reflects your individual style and comfort. Your rings are a pair, not necessarily twins. You can coordinate them by choosing the same metal or a similar finish.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "accordion_BRezAN": {
          "type": "accordion",
          "settings": {
            "accordion_header": "Which metal is best for a wedding band?",
            "open_by_default": false,
            "text": "<p>The \"best\" metal depends on your lifestyle and preference. Platinum is the most durable and is naturally hypoallergenic. 18ct Gold (Yellow, White, or Rose) is the classic choice, offering a rich colour. We can discuss the pros and cons of each during your consultation.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        }
      },
